<task id="task-2539" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Use OAuth 1.0 Authorization in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/></title><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context ">To use OAuth 1.0 authorization in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/>, do as follows:</context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Authorization</uicontrol> tab of a web service request, set the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Type</uicontrol> as <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">OAuth 1.0</uicontrol>.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><image width="700" href="ks-840-choose-oauth01.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">authorization tab</alt></image></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Fill in your authorization information , then click on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Update to HTTP Header</uicontrol>.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><image width="700" href="ks-840-oauth01-authorization.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">OAuth 1.0 authentication</alt></image></info></step></steps><result class="- topic/section task/result ">The authorization information are updated  to the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Authorization</uicontrol> request of the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">HTTP Header</uicontrol> tab, as you can see below.<p class="- topic/p "><image width="700" href="ks-840-oauth-01-http-header.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">http header</alt></image></p></result></taskbody></task>